
README
------

This is FirebirdBBS 2.5 quick installation guide.

The installation document and administration guide  is in 
~bbsroot/doc/README.txt.

For impatient users, 

1. Create the following three accounts, and their home directories:

bbsroot::9990:99:BBS and modify source code:/home/bbsroot:/bin/csh
bbs::9999:99:BBS user:/home/bbs:/home/bbs/bin/bbsrf
bbsuser::9999:99:BBS user:/home/bbs:/bin/csh

2. Add the group 'bbs' into /etc/group

bbs:*:99:bbsroot,bbsuser,bbs

3. Run the following commands

% tar zxvf FirebirdBBS2.5.tar.gz 
% cd bbs_src
% ( cd CONFIG ; ./configure )
% make
% su
# make install

4. telnet localhost 

5. login as 'bbs'

6. Hope you can see the 'welcome' message from the BBS.

                                       from developers of FirebirdBBS 2.5 

                                                            Nov 22.

